==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#An expression (sometimes a figure of speech) with an inclination toward western civilization (i.e. the occident). 
       ''A kind of '''occidentotropism''' ("Go West Young Man"!) informs the films, conveying 
       a thrusting purposiveness...: ''Red Sundown'' (1956), ''Union Pacific'' (1939), ''The 
       Last Outpost'' (1935, 1951), ''Heaven's Gate'' (1959).''
              - Ella Shohat and Robert Stam, "The Imperial Imaginary"



